# Proposal Writer — ai-chatbot-for-customer-support

## Deliverables Produced

All three proposal artifacts written and built to:
`upwork-runs/ai-chatbot-for-customer-support/proposal/`

### cover-letter.md (2.5 KB)
- Hook: names the repetitive-support problem directly
- Demo link front-loaded (second paragraph): https://michaelwegter.com/demos/ai-chatbot-for-customer-support/
- Describes what the demo does (FAQ KB, order lookup ORD-1001, escalation, admin panel, in-browser AI)
- Real-build architecture explained concisely (Transformers.js RAG, Zendesk Web Widget SDK, real order API swap-in)
- Proof points: U.S. Bank (2.5yr, 600 users/mo, 60k LOC), Optum (current, Angular/.NET)
- Timeline: 7 to 8 business days
- Pricing: $2,500 to $4,500 fixed price with rationale
- US confirmation: "I am currently based in the United States" stated explicitly
- No em/en dashes

### one-pager.html (20 KB)
- Bespoke SaaS support-tool design: DM Sans + Inter, slate-900 dark header, blue-600 accent, green-500 highlights
- Sections: hero with demo badge, 3 screenshots, 4 feature cards, in-browser RAG architecture diagram, requirements checklist, Zendesk 4-step flow, 3-tier pricing table, timeline table, about card with US confirmation, footer
- Screenshots embedded from media/: 01-hero.png, 02-chat-ready.png, 03-admin-dashboard.png
- No portfolio theme (no mustard/cyan/Space Grotesk)
- No em/en dashes

### build_deck.py + deck.pptx (742 KB, 9 slides)
- Palette: slate-900 BG, blue-400 accent, green-500 eyebrows, Inter + DM Sans
- Slide 1: Title + demo badge
- Slide 2: The Problem (4 pain-point cards)
- Slide 3: The Solution (4 feature cards)
- Slide 4: Demo screenshots (all 3 media files embedded)
- Slide 5: Architecture (4-node RAG pipeline + zero-cost callout)
- Slide 6: Zendesk integration design (4-step flow)
- Slide 7: Timeline + 3-tier pricing
- Slide 8: About Michael (4 proof-point cards + US confirmation)
- Slide 9: CTA with demo URL
- No em/en dashes (assert_no_dashes enforced on every text call)

## Requirement Traceability

| Requirement | Addressed |
|---|---|
| Architecture explanation | Cover letter para 3, deck slide 5, one-pager architecture section |
| Examples of similar work | Cover letter (demo = the example), one-pager demo screenshots |
| Timeline + price breakdown | Cover letter, deck slide 7, one-pager pricing/timeline section |
| Fixed vs hourly recommendation | Fixed price recommended with rationale in all three deliverables |
| US confirmation | Cover letter explicit statement, deck slide 1 + 8, one-pager about card |
| Demo link in cover letter | Yes, second paragraph |
| Demo link in deck | Slides 1, 4, 9 |
| No em/en dashes | Enforced via assert_no_dashes in deck; verified in cover letter and one-pager |

